1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,953
Begin with the artifact, not the activity.

2
00:00:02,903 --> 00:00:05,666
Help with this project” describes effort.

3
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:11,798
Produce a decision memo comparing the three launch options” describes something another person can review and use.

4
00:00:11,798 --> 00:00:22,836
OpenAI's examples include briefs, summaries, decks, workbooks, plans, process documents, daily updates, launch kits, financial reviews, and workflow audits.

5
00:00:22,836 --> 00:00:27,625
These are useful because each one has a visible shape and a next decision attached to it.

6
00:00:27,625 --> 00:00:30,471
Name the artifact in operational terms.

7
00:00:30,471 --> 00:00:36,778
State who will use it, what decision or action it supports, and what state counts as a first usable version.

8
00:00:36,778 --> 00:00:42,490
A first version is not final, but it must be complete enough to reveal missing facts and weak reasoning.

9
00:00:42,490 --> 00:00:45,336
Separate the deliverable from the larger goal.

10
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:48,038
Improve customer retention” is a goal.

11
00:00:48,038 --> 00:00:55,903
A cohort analysis with three prioritized hypotheses, supporting evidence, and owners is an artifact that can move that goal forward.

12
00:00:55,903 --> 00:00:58,894
Use a verb plus an object plus a decision.

13
00:00:58,894 --> 00:01:03,375
Draft the weekly operating brief so team leads can identify blocked work.

14
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:07,711
Build the launch checklist so the release owner can approve or stop the rollout.

15
00:01:07,711 --> 00:01:11,961
Turn scattered research into a comparison table so the buyer can choose.

16
00:01:11,961 --> 00:01:15,913
The common failure is requesting motion without defining completion.

17
00:01:15,913 --> 00:01:21,596
The agent searches, summarizes, and writes, but neither side knows when the task is done.

18
00:01:21,596 --> 00:01:26,653
A named artifact creates an end state and gives every later constraint a place to attach.

19
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:30,711
First, define a concrete artifact before describing the work.

20
00:01:30,711 --> 00:01:34,634
Second, connect that artifact to a real user and decision.

21
00:01:34,634 --> 00:01:38,800
Third, make the first version usable enough to expose what is missing.
